Since your question is about the `operator +=` function, I will focus on that. The following should work:
```
template&lt;class T&gt;
Bag&lt;T&gt; &amp; Bag&lt;T&gt;::operator += (const Bag&lt;T&gt;&amp; a_bag)
{
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; a_bag.item_count_; i++) {
        add(a_bag.items_[i]);
    }
    return *this;
}
```
By convention the `operator +=` modifies the left hand side (`this`) by adding/appending the right hand side (`a_bag`). Hence no new object is created, but a reference to the left hand side, i.e. (`*this`) is returned which allows the `=+` expression to be part of a larger expression, e.g. an argument in a function call.

